    <text id="F8014T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Curtin discusses possible patronage appointments.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="underline">Private</hi>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860"><del rend="none" hand="h1"/> 11, <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> 1860</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <unclear>Bellefonte</unclear>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My <orig reg="dear">der</orig> Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I write you in response to our friend Taggart and as you <unclear>just to assume
                        from</unclear> you did not receive my letter.</p>
                <p>I am of the opinion that we cannot get the <unclear>collectorship</unclear> for
                    him, and <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> the help to get him some honorable and lucrative
                    place--</p>
                <p>As several of your friends named <unclear>Mr Pluncual</unclear> for <abbr
                        expan="Attorney General">Atty Gen</abbr> it will no doubt be gratifying to
                    you to hear that I think of appointing him.</p>
                <p>I will be pleased to hear from you.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Yours">Yrs</abbr> truly</salute>
                    <signed>A. G. Curtin</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr>
                            <abbr expan="Simon">S.</abbr> Cameron</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
